	// be used to reliably identify an output in e.g. configuration files.
	//
	// Examples of names include 'HDMI-A-1', 'WL-1', 'X11-1', etc. However, do
	// not assume that the name is a reflection of an underlying DRM connector,
	// X11 connection, etc.
